1. Start
2. Input two strings:
      s (source string)
      t (target string)
3. Compute:
       n = length of s
       m = length of t
4. Create a DP array dp of size m + 1
       Initialize all values to 0
5. Base Case:
       Set dp[0] = 1
6. Iterate through string s:
       For i = 1 to n:
7. Traverse t backwards
       For j = m down to 1:
If characters match:
       if s[i-1] == t[j-1]
            dp[j] = dp[j] + dp[j-1]
8. Final Result:
       The number of distinct subsequences = dp[m]
9. Return (int)dp[m]
10. End
